<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1922-11-18T08:00:00-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1922-11-18T08:00:00-05:00" n="551" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d551">
                        <note rend="inline" type="source">893.113/391: Telegram</note>
                        <head><hi rend="italic">The Chargé in Italy</hi> (<persName type="from"><hi rend="italic">Gunther</hi></persName>) <hi rend="italic">to the
                                    <gloss type="to">Secretary of State</gloss></hi></head>
                        <opener><dateline rendition="#right"><placeName><hi rend="smallcaps">Rome</hi></placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1922-11-18T14:00:00+01:00"><hi rend="italic">November 18,
                                        1922—2 p.m.</hi></date><lb/>[Received November 18—11:25
                                a.m.]</dateline></opener>
                        <p>231. Department’s 148, October 17, 5 p.m.<note n="9" xml:id="d551fn9">See
                                footnote 4, <ref target="#pg_757">p. 757</ref>.</note> Evasive reply
                            received from Foreign Office states Italian Government has no objection
                            to United States inviting Powers mentioned to give their assent to the
                            proposals contained in Department’s 56, May 4, 2 p.m., to [<hi rend="italic">via?</hi>] Paris<note n="10" xml:id="d551fn10">See
                                footnote 91, <ref target="#pg_748">p. 748</ref>.</note> and 107,
                            July 25, 2 [<hi rend="italic">3</hi>] p.m.<note n="11" xml:id="d551fn11">Not printed.</note> Effort being made to secure definite assurance
                            of adherence to proposals outlined in Department’s 148, October 27 [<hi rend="italic">17</hi>], 5 p.m. via Paris.</p>
                        <closer><signed><hi rend="smallcaps">Gunther</hi></signed></closer>
                    </div>
                    </body></text></TEI>